# Folds

A fold collapses a range of lines to one summary line — for navigation, not
editing (the text is untouched). How folds form is set by `foldmethod`; the
`z`-prefixed keys open, close, and move between them.

## Fold method — `:set foldmethod=`

| Method | Folds by |
|--------|----------|
| `manual` | folds you create by hand (`zf`) |
| `indent` | indentation level (`shiftwidth`) |
| `marker` | `{{{` / `}}}` markers in the text |
| `syntax` | syntax regions (language-aware) |
| `expr` | `foldexpr` — e.g. nvim treesitter (@nvim/treesitter) |
| `diff` | unchanged regions in diff mode (@vim/diff) |

## Create (manual / marker)

| Key | Does |
|-----|------|
| `zf{motion}` | create a fold over a motion/text-object (`zfap`, `zf}`) |
| `:{range}fold` | create a fold over an ex range (@vim/ex) |
| `zd` / `zD` / `zE` | delete fold / recursively / all in window |

## Open, close, toggle

| Key | Does |
|-----|------|
| `zo` / `zc` / `za` | open / close / toggle one fold |
| `zO` / `zC` / `zA` | …recursively (nested folds too) |
| `zR` / `zM` | open all / close all folds |
| `zr` / `zm` | open / close one more level everywhere |
| `zv` | open just enough to see the cursor line |

## Navigate

| Key | To |
|-----|----|
| `zj` / `zk` | start of next / end of previous fold |
| `[z` / `]z` | start / end of the current open fold |
| `:set foldlevel=N` | open folds shallower than level N |
| `:set foldcolumn=N` | show a fold-indicator gutter N columns wide |
